  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Keeping poor girls in school will close the gender educational gap in Vietnam and strengthen families and improve community life.  Women&apos;s Empowerment and Voice (WEAV) has been awarding primary, secondary, and university scholarships to needy and motivated  girls and women in the Mekong Delta and Greater Saigon since 2012.  WEAV has a vast network of universities and schools;their demand for scholarships are increasing by 10% annually.  WEAV works with ethnic minority communities in the delta!</narrative>
